<plot>Old wounds collide with new realities when a Vietnamese shopkeeper challenges the heart of the Vietnamese-American community with symbols of the communist regime from which they fled. Massive protests in Orange County's Little Saigon raise questions about individual versus community rights, generational differences, what it means to be Vietnamese-American and, ultimately, what it means to be American.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?473984</url></doc>
